# Data Layer & Cloud Sync

## Feature Flag

`USE_SUPABASE` in `src/database/config.ts` controls the active data backend. When `false`: localStorage + GitHub API. When `true`: Supabase PostgreSQL via `supabaseCache.ts`.

## Supabase Architecture (Migration)

### Schema
- **20 tables** in `supabase/schema.sql`: groups, group_members, players, player_traits, games, game_players, game_forecasts, shared_expenses, paid_settlements, period_markers, chip_values, settings, pending_forecasts, chronicle_profiles, graph_insights, tts_pools, activity_log, training_pool, training_answers, training_insights
- **Auth functions** in `supabase/002-auth-support.sql`: create_group, join_group_by_invite, link_member_to_player
- All tables have **Row Level Security (RLS)** policies enforcing group-level isolation via `auth.uid()` + `group_id`
- UUIDs for all primary keys; foreign keys enforce referential integrity

### Cache Layer (`supabaseCache.ts`)
- In-memory cache mirroring localStorage format for backward compatibility
- `initSupabaseCache(groupId)` loads all data from Supabase on startup
- Reads are synchronous from cache; writes debounce async pushes to Supabase
- **Denormalization on read**: Supabase normalized tables → flat localStorage objects (e.g., game + shared_expenses + period_markers → single Game object)
- **Normalization on write**: Flat objects → separate Supabase table inserts/upserts
- **Delete sync**: When items are removed from cache (shared_expenses, game_players), corresponding Supabase rows are explicitly deleted

### Migration Script (`migrateToSupabase.ts`)
- One-time migration from localStorage to Supabase
- Generates new UUIDs, maintains IdMap for cross-references
- Handles orphaned player references (creates placeholders or nulls FK)
- `checkGroupHasData()` prevents double-migration
- `cleanGroupData()` for retry wipes

### Dual-Branch Functions
Files with `USE_SUPABASE` branches:
- `src/database/storage.ts` — all ~76 data access functions
- `src/database/githubSync.ts` — 7 training functions (fetchTrainingPool, uploadTrainingPool, fetchTrainingAnswers, writeTrainingAnswersWithRetry, fetchTrainingInsights, uploadTrainingInsights, removeFromTrainingPool)
- `src/utils/activityLogger.ts` — 6 activity functions (logActivity, updateSessionActivity, fetchActivityLog, deleteActivityEntry, deleteDeviceEntries, clearActivityLog)

